Cape Town - Metro police officers arrested a suspected for stealing chicken and potato chips worth R3000 on Thursday morning. At around 9am, officers on patrol in Woodlands, Mitchells Plain noticed two men walking down the road, pushing a shopping trolley. The goods in the trolley had been covered with clothing, piquing the officersâ€™ interest. When they stopped to investigate, one of the men ran away. The second tried to get away too, but was unsuccessful. When officers searched the trolley, they found 30 bags of chicken (3kg each) and half a dozen bags of potato chips (5kg each). The goods were valued at around R3 000. It later emerged that the items were stolen from a fast food outlet in Westgate Mall. The 26-year-old suspect was detained at Lentegeur SAPS. Cape Argus